    • Method Detail

      • onLocationChanged

        void onLocationChanged​(@NonNull
                       LocationProvider locationProvider,
                       @NonNull
                       Location location)
        Callback for when the location changes or when the status changes. For example if the GPS is invalid, the onLocationChanged would be fired with the location provider and the location object set with the isValid flag set to false.
        Parameters:
        locationProvider - the location provider for the location change
        location - the location

      • rawLocationCallback

        void rawLocationCallback​(@NonNull
                         LocationProvider locationProvider,
                         @NonNull
                         java.lang.String type,
                         @NonNull
                         byte[] data)
        Called if there is raw data that is changing for the location provider
        Parameters:
        locationProvider - the location provider for the raw data change
        type - the type of data such as NMEA, etc.
        data - the byte array of the data
